Description.LocalizedString:
A metal box containing mainly saws and vice grips of varying sizes but also other tools. Even though the content of this Toolbox is clearly aimed at destructive deeds, it can be used to repair various mechanical components as well.
  • 18 charges.
  • Increases repair speed by 10%.
  • Unlocks the sabotage action.
  • Increases sabotage speed by 100%.

    • Repairing a generator requires 90 charges.
    Sabotaging a hook requires 6 charges.

    "Most of the tools are identified as 'owned by Alex'."

InGameDescription.LocalizedString: Use Item button: Repair Generators +10% faster or Sabotage Hooks for up to 18s. +100% Sabotage speed.

Description.LocalizedString:
An old piece of parchment made out of a skin-like material. It is rolled and sealed with an uncolored leather string. Holding and channeling the Map unlocks great potential in one's aura reading ability which slowly burns the Map. Generators' auras which you have already encountered are revealed to you for as long as the Map has charges left.
  • 20 seconds of use.
  • Start with 1 generator automatically tracked.
  • Unlocks the ability to track generators within a 8 meter range.

InGameDescription.LocalizedString: Use Item button: You see the aura of tracked objects for up to 20s.

Description.LocalizedString:
The bow and shank of a key, vibrating with power. The broken key's power cannot be triggered by itself. Various objects can be attached to its jump ring, which channels the broken key's power into various effects.
  • 10 seconds of use.

InGameDescription.LocalizedString: Use Item button: Trigger its add-ons for up to 10s.

Description.LocalizedString:
A large metal box containing basic tools and extra mechanical parts. Even without training, can be used to repair or break various mechanical components.
  • 32 charges.
  • Increases repair speed by 50%.
  • Unlocks the sabotage action.
  • Increases sabotage speed by 50%.

    • Repairing a generator requires 90 charges.
    Sabotaging a hook requires 6 charges.

InGameDescription.LocalizedString: Use Item button: Repair Generators +50% faster or Sabotage Hooks for up to 32s. +50% Sabotage speed.

Description.LocalizedString:
A bent and dull Key that once held great power. The Key's power cannot be triggered by itself. Various objects can be attached to its jump ring, which channels the Dull Key's remaining power into various effects.
  • 5 seconds of use.
  • Can be consumed to open the Hatch.

InGameDescription.LocalizedString: Use Item button: Trigger its add-ons for up to 5s. Use Item button: Open and escape through the Hatch.

Description.LocalizedString:
Metal box with highly specialized tools meant for engineering. Most of the tools can still be used by neophytes to make fast repairs or break various mechanical components.
  • 16 charges.
  • Increases repair speed by 100%.
  • Unlocks the sabotage action.
  • Increases sabotage speed by 10%.

    • Repairing a generator requires 90 charges.
    Sabotaging a hook requires 6 charges.

    "I've created tools beyond compare and stood paralyzed as they were stolen from me. These are but a poor replica, spat out by The Fog." –Vigo's Journal

InGameDescription.LocalizedString: Use Item button: Repair Generators +100% faster or Sabotage Hooks for up to 16s. +10% Sabotage speed.

Description.LocalizedString:
A row of small explosive devices wrapped in heavy paper casing. Detonates into loud bangs and intense light flashes. Can be used as a distraction, as a blinding device or to celebrate.
  • 1 charge.

InGameDescription.LocalizedString: Use Item button: Detonates it blinding and deafening any nearby Players.

Description.LocalizedString:
A standard Flashlight. Can be used to light your way in the darkness.
  • 8 seconds of use.

    • "Most of the battery life was wastefully used by the previous owner."

InGameDescription.LocalizedString: Use Item button: Attempt to blind the killer for up to 8s.

Description.LocalizedString:
A very portable Flashlight with a good grip. Its efficient technology produces a powerful light while consuming less power.
  • 8 Seconds of use.
  • Decreases Flashlight battery consumption by 11%.
  • Increases the accuracy of the Flashlight beam by 20%.

InGameDescription.LocalizedString: Use Item button: Attempt to blind the killer for up to 8s. +20% Accuracy, -11% Battery Consumption

Description.LocalizedString:
A sturdy but heavy Flashlight that packs a lot of power.
  • 12 Seconds of use.
  • Increases the brightness of the Flashlight beam by 30%.
  • Increases Blindness duration by 15%.
  • Decreases the accuracy of the Flashlight beam by 20%.

InGameDescription.LocalizedString: Use Item button: Attempt to blind the killer for up to 12s. +30% Brightness, +15% Duration, -20% Accuracy

Description.LocalizedString:
A tarnished and crooked key, vibrating with ominous power. The key's power cannot be triggered by itself. Various objects can be attached to its jump ring, which channels the Skeleton Key's power into various effects.
  • 30 seconds of use.
  • Can be consumed to open the Hatch.

InGameDescription.LocalizedString: Use Item button: Trigger its add-ons for up to 30s. Use Item button: Open and escape through the Hatch.

Description.LocalizedString:
Metal box with specialized mechanics tools. Even without training, can be used to repair or break various mechanical components.
  • 16 charges.
  • Increases repair speed by 75%.
  • Unlocks the sabotage action.
  • Increases sabotage speed by 25%.

    • Repairing a generator requires 90 charges.
    Sabotaging a hook requires 6 charges.

InGameDescription.LocalizedString: Use Item button: Repair Generators +75% faster or Sabotage Hooks for up to 16s. +25% Sabotage speed.

Description.LocalizedString:
A rudimentary aid kit which can save lives in emergencies, even if it's lacking some of its supplies.
  • 24 charges.
  • Increases the speed that you heal others by 35%.
  • Unlocks the self-healing action.
  • Decreases the speed and efficiency when healing yourself by 33%.

    • A full heal requires 16 charges.

    "Barely has enough material for a decent patch-up."

InGameDescription.LocalizedString: Use Item button: Heal other Survivors +35% faster or yourself for up to 24s.

Description.LocalizedString:
A standard first aid kit with all the necessary equipment for treating common to more serious injuries.
  • 24 charges.
  • Increases the speed that you heal others by 40%.
  • Unlocks the self-healing action.
  • Decreases the speed and efficiency when healing yourself by 33%.

    • A full heal requires 16 charges.

InGameDescription.LocalizedString: Use Item button: Heal other Survivors +40% faster or yourself for up to 24s.

Description.LocalizedString:
A sturdy and well organized medical kit equipped with top condition emergency supplies.
  • 24 charges.
  • Increases the speed that you heal others by 45%.
  • Unlocks the self-healing action.
  • Decreases the speed and efficiency when healing yourself by 33%.

    • A full heal requires 16 charges.

    "There is a cure for almost everything… but not for this."

InGameDescription.LocalizedString: Use Item button: Heal other Survivors +45% faster or yourself for up to 24s.

Description.LocalizedString:
A large metal box containing medical supplies aimed for emergency rescues in hard to reach, often isolated locations.
  • 24 charges.
  • Increases the speed that you heal others by 50%.
  • Unlocks the self-healing action.
  • Decreases the speed and efficiency when healing yourself by 33%.

    • A full heal requires 16 charges.

    "A small engraved label can be found glued to the back panel: VK.ID-3994723."

InGameDescription.LocalizedString: Use Item button: Heal other Survivors +50% faster or yourself for up to 24s.

Description.LocalizedString:
A piece of parchment made out of oddly fresh skin. Blood on its edge has yet to dry. It is rolled and sealed with multiple colored ropes and cords. Holding and channelling the Map unlocks great potential in one's aura reading ability which slowly burns up the Map. Objects with auras which you have already encountered are revealed to you for as long as the Map has charges left.
  • 20 seconds of use.
  • Start with 3 objects automatically tracked.
  • Unlocks the ability to track objectives within an 8 meter range.
  • Unlocks the ability to track the Hatch within an 8 meter range.
  • Unlocks the ability to track the Killer's belongings within an 8 meter range.
  • Unlocks the ability to track the exit gates within an 8 meter range.

    • "It disheartens me. All this unspeakable knowledge and gruelling effort and yet nothing tangible, nothing usable to get out of this nightmare." -Vigo's Journal

InGameDescription.LocalizedString: Use Item button: You see the aura of tracked objects for up to 20s. +Track extra objects

Description.LocalizedString:
Metal box containing a set of basic tools. Even without training, can be used to repair or break various mechanical components.
  • 20 charges.
  • Increases repair speed by 50%.
  • Unlocks the sabotage action.
  • Increases sabotage speed by 15%.

    • Repairing a generator requires 90 charges.
    Sabotaging a hook requires 6 charges.

    "It is unclear as to where these tools come from. Were they brought in by one of us or did they belong to one of the monsters?"

InGameDescription.LocalizedString: Use Item button: Repair Generators +50% faster or Sabotage Hooks for up to 20s. +15% Sabotage speed.

Description.LocalizedString:
Metal box containing out of condition tools that could break at any moment. Even without training, can be used to repair or break various mechanical components.
  • 16 charges.
  • Increases repair speed by 50%.
  • Decreases Skill Check success zone size by 10%.
  • Unlocks the sabotage action.

    • Repairing a generator requires 90 charges.
    Sabotaging a hook requires 6 charges.

    "You call these tools?… Really?"

InGameDescription.LocalizedString: Use Item button: Repair Generators +50% faster or Sabotage Hooks for up to 16s. -10% Skill Check size

Description.LocalizedString:
A large foothold trap made of steel. Traps are found lying around the area waiting to be picked up and set anywhere.

BEAR TRAP
By default, you start the trial with 2 Bear Traps. Find and collect more throughout the environment.

Set Bear Trap:
Press and hold the Power button to set a Bear Trap on a valid location in front of you. A set Bear Trap will immobilize and incapacitate any player that steps on it. A healthy Survivor that steps in a set Bear Trap will also become injured but may attempt to escape the trap. Press the Interaction button to pick-up a nearby Survivor who is Incapacitated by a Bear Trap.

Reset Trap:
Press and hold the Power button while standing near a Bear Trap in the environment to reset it where it lies, if it is not already set.

Collect Bear Trap:
Press the Interaction button while standing near a Bear Trap in the environment to collect it. By default, you may carry a maximum of 2 Bear Traps at any time.

The machine gave him a new life, one where the power was in his hands.

Press and hold the Power button to break into a Chainsaw Sprint. Survivors hit during a Chainsaw Sprint are put into the dying state.

Revving the chainsaw, and sprinting each cause the Overdrive meter to increase. The meter decreases when the chainsaw is not in use.

When the meter is full, the chainsaw goes into Overdrive.

SPECIAL STATE: OVERDRIVE
While in Overdrive, the chainsaw is enhanced. Chainsaw Charge and Sprint speeds are increased, and Chainsaw Sprint cooldowns are reduced.

Overdrive lasts for 20 seconds.

The source of The Hag's power, a blackened finger used as a catalyst for her terrible power. The Hag bends and shapes mud to her will. With simple ritualistic drawings, she creates deceitful duplicates of herself made from mud and decay which she can use for various effects.
  • Grants the ability to create and maintain 10 Phantasm Traps.
  • Grants the ability to instantly travel to triggered Phantasm Traps when within a 48 meter range.
